  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="mb-16" data-controller="accordion">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">

      <div class="bg-zinc-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-zinc-800" data-accordion-target="item">
        <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-5 text-left" data-action="click->accordion#toggle">
          <span class="font-medium text-white pr-4">Can I switch plans later?</span>
          <svg data-role="icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div data-role="answer" class="overflow-hidden transition-all duration-200" style="max-height: 0px;">
          <p class="px-5 pb-5 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. You can upgrade or downgrade at any time. When you upgrade, you get immediate access to the new features. When you downgrade, the change takes effect at the end of your billing cycle.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-zinc-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-zinc-800" data-accordion-target="item">
        <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-5 text-left" data-action="click->accordion#toggle">
          <span class="font-medium text-white pr-4">Do you offer annual billing?</span>
          <svg data-role="icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div data-role="answer" class="overflow-hidden transition-all duration-200" style="max-height: 0px;">
          <p class="px-5 pb-5 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Yes! Use the toggle above to see annual pricing. You save 23% compared to monthly billing. Annual plans are billed as a single payment for the year.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-zinc-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-zinc-800" data-accordion-target="item">
        <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-5 text-left" data-action="click->accordion#toggle">
          <span class="font-medium text-white pr-4">What happens when I hit a plan limit?</span>
          <svg data-role="icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div data-role="answer" class="overflow-hidden transition-all duration-200" style="max-height: 0px;">
          <p class="px-5 pb-5 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            We'll let you know before you hit a limit and give you the option to upgrade. Your existing articles and help centre stay live &mdash; we never take published content offline because of plan limits.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-zinc-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-zinc-800" data-accordion-target="item">
        <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-5 text-left" data-action="click->accordion#toggle">
          <span class="font-medium text-white pr-4">How does the Docker container work on Enterprise?</span>
          <svg data-role="icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div data-role="answer" class="overflow-hidden transition-all duration-200" style="max-height: 0px;">
          <p class="px-5 pb-5 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            On the Enterprise plan, we provide a Docker image you run in your own CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins, etc.). The container analyses your code locally and sends only the generated article content back to SupportPages. Your source code never leaves your infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

